Program: Outlook
Title: Life Before and After the Berlin Wall
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p02b0dwj
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 12 Nov 2014
Uwe Tellkamp is an author who was brought up in East Germany. He has used his family's experiences of the country's repressive communist regime as the basis of his prize winning novel called The Tower. Tahir Qadiry meets the skate-kids of Mazar-e-Sharif in Afghanistan, who are combining skateboarding and schooling. James Wharton was one of the first openly gay British soldiers. He has written a book about his experiences called Out In The Army. Saad Haroon is a comedian from Pakistan who's just been voted the second funniest person in the world. Show less